---
import BgGrid from "@/components/assets/BgGrid.astro";
---

<section class="border-b border-white/10 bg-[#0a0a0a] overflow-hidden">
  <div class="px-8 py-12 relative border-b border-white/10">
    <BgGrid />
    <p class="text-[#ff5f1f] font-mono text-[10px] mb-4 tracking-[0.4em] uppercase opacity-60 relative">
      // Featured Architecture
    </p>
    <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-white uppercase tracking-tighter relative">
      Case Study: <span class="text-[#ff5f1f]">CVE-RSS Alert System</span>
    </h2>
  </div>

  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-12">
    <div class="lg:col-span-7 p-8 md:p-16 border-b lg:border-b-0 lg:border-r border-white/10">
      
      <div class="mb-16">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-4">
          <span class="text-[#ff5f1f] font-mono text-xl">01</span>
          <h3 class="text-white text-2xl font-bold uppercase italic">Problem Analysis</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="text-white/60 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl mb-4">
          Security teams face "Alert Fatigue" from manual monitoring of NVD and CISA databases. Manually parsing RSS feeds results in a <strong>4-6 hour delay</strong> between vulnerability publication and internal triage, leaving a critical window open for exploitation.
        </p>
        <div class="flex gap-2">
          <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-red-500/10 border border-red-500/20 text-red-500 text-[10px] uppercase font-mono">Slow Response</span>
          <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-red-500/10 border border-red-500/20 text-red-500 text-[10px] uppercase font-mono">Manual Triage</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-16">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-4">
          <span class="text-[#ff5f1f] font-mono text-xl">02</span>
          <h3 class="text-white text-2xl font-bold uppercase italic">Solution Design</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="text-white/60 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
          I designed an event-driven pipeline using <strong>n8n</strong> to automate the entire lifecycle of a vulnerability. The system architecture includes:
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm text-white/80 font-light">
          <li class="flex gap-2">
            <span class="text-[#ff5f1f]">→</span> 
            <strong>CISA/NVD Ingestion:</strong> Real-time polling via RSS and REST API.
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-2">
            <span class="text-[#ff5f1f]">→</span> 
            <strong>State Management:</strong> Google Sheets acts as a lightweight DB to track "Seen" CVEs and prevent alert duplication.
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-2">
            <span class="text-[#ff5f1f]">→</span> 
            <strong>Dynamic Risk Scoring:</strong> Custom JS node to parse multi-version CVSS (3.1, 3.0, 2.0) and route by severity.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div>
          <h4 class="text-white font-bold uppercase text-xs tracking-widest mb-4 opacity-40">The Stack</h4>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
            {["n8n", "NVD API v2.0", "Regex", "Javascript", "Google Sheets", "Gmail"].map(tech => (
              <span class="text-[10px] font-mono text-white/40 border border-white/5 px-2 py-1">{tech}</span>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="text-white font-bold uppercase text-xs tracking-widest mb-4 opacity-40">Impact Metrics</h4>
          <ul class="text-[#ff5f1f] font-mono text-xs space-y-1">
            <li>+ 95% Reduction in Triage Time</li>
            <li>+ Zero Duplicated Alerts</li>
            <li>+ Instant Critical Notification</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="lg:col-span-5 bg-white/[0.02] p-8 md:p-16 flex flex-col justify-center">
      <div class="border border-white/10 p-6 bg-black/40 backdrop-blur-sm relative">
        <div class="absolute -top-3 -left-3 bg-[#ff5f1f] text-black text-[10px] font-black px-2 py-1 uppercase">
          Logic: Risk_Scoring.js
        </div>
        <pre class="text-[11px] leading-relaxed text-white/40 overflow-x-auto">
<code>{`// Extracted from n8n Workflow
if (score >= 9) {
  severity = "CRITICAL";
  decision = "alert"; // Instant Gmail
} else if (score >= 7.5) {
  severity = "HIGH";
  decision = "review"; // Manual Check
} else {
  severity = "LOW/MED";
  decision = "log"; // Audit Only
}`}</code>
        </pre>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12">
        <h4 class="text-white text-xl font-bold uppercase mb-4">Lessons Learned</h4>
        <p class="text-white/50 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-6">
          The biggest challenge was handling the NVD API rate limits and data inconsistency between CVSS versions. I optimized the workflow by implementing a <strong>Lookup node</strong> that only queries the API if the CVE is not already in the audit log, saving hundreds of unnecessary API calls daily.
        </p>
        <a 
          href="https://github.com/Dessybabybaby/cve-rss-alert-system" 
          target="_blank"
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-[#ff5f1f] text-[10px] font-black uppercase tracking-widest hover:underline"
        >
          View Full JSON Workflow 
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="size-3" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><path d="M7 17L17 7M7 7h10v10"/></svg>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>